[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] > Extended question types and templates for listening exercises, designed to increase question count and variety per exercise.
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] ---
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] ## 1. Question Types Overview
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] | `true-false` | True / False / Not Given statements | `options?` (reused for the 3 choices) |
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] |------|-------------|------------|
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] | `short-answer` | Short written response (1–3 words) | `acceptableAnswers?` on model, or reuse `blanks` |
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] **Proposed `ListeningQuestionType` additions:**
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] [0m
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] | Type | Description | New fields |
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] | `multiple-answer` | Select N correct options from a list | `correctAnswer` as `number[]` |
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] | `table-completion` | Fill cells in a structured table from the recording | `blanks`, `rows`, `columns` (new optional field) |
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] The current `ListeningQuestionType` supports `multiple-choice` and `gap-fill`. The following new types are designed to be compatible with the existing `ListeningQuestion` interface, requiring only an extension of the type union.
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] ## 2. Type: True / False / Not Given
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] ---
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] ### Data Structure (compatible with `ListeningQuestion`)
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] A statement is provided. The candidate selects **True** (the recording confirms it), **False** (the recording contradicts it), or **Not Given** (the recording does not address it).
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] ### Format
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr]   id: string
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] ```typescript
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr]   correctAnswer: number     // Index into options: 0=True, 1=False, 2=Not Given
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] }
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] | `sentence-completion` | Complete sentences from the recording (multiple gaps) | `blanks` (already supported) |
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr]   explanation: string
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] {
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr]   question: string          // The statement to evaluate
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr]   type: 'true-false'
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] ### Example Questions
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr] ```
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.774Z] [INFO] [stderr]   options: ['True', 'False', 'Not Given']
