[2026-07-04T06:05:51.775Z] [INFO] [stderr]   options: string[]         // All available choices
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.775Z] [INFO] [stderr]   id: string
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.775Z] [INFO] [stderr]   question: string
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.775Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.775Z] [INFO] [stderr] }
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.775Z] [INFO] [stderr] ```
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.775Z] [INFO] [stderr]   explanation: string
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.775Z] [INFO] [stderr] > Note: `correctAnswer` currently accepts `string | number | string[]`. The value `"1,3,4"` (a string) is compatible. Alternatively, `correctAnswer` could be `number[]` — the model already supports `string[]`.
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.775Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.775Z] [INFO] [stderr]   correctAnswer: string     // Comma-separated indices of correct options, e.g., "1,3,4"
[2026-07-04T06:05:51.775Z] [INFO] [stderr] 
